00:16:49,386 --> 00:16:51,908
changing the odds a level below that, within the odds.

374
00:16:52,369 --> 00:16:55,593
So they don't even need to change their disclosures to comply with Apple's terms.

375
00:16:57,502 --> 00:17:01,424
It's conceivable that they might get an action for fraud

376
00:17:01,464 --> 00:17:02,084
brought against them.

377
00:17:02,584 --> 00:17:03,925
But if they have a good lawyer, they're

378
00:17:03,985 --> 00:17:06,706
probably going to be OK right now in the United States.

379
00:17:07,927 --> 00:17:08,767
What about the EU?

380
00:17:09,387 --> 00:17:12,309
Similar answer, although I'd say EU courts are

381
00:17:12,349 --> 00:17:14,930
sort of more favorable to sort of creative legal actions.

382
00:17:15,110 --> 00:17:16,911
So even though there's no strict law prohibiting it,

383
00:17:17,351 --> 00:17:19,031
probably slightly riskier in the EU.

384
00:17:19,612 --> 00:17:21,933
Obviously, you can't do this in Belgium.

385
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,294
I think you could still do it in Holland,

386
00:17:24,354 --> 00:17:25,854
as long as you didn't restrict transfers.

387
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:28,690
So what about China, the country we just talked about?

388
00:17:29,071 --> 00:17:32,152
Well, this violates the formal rules for a lot of reasons.

389
00:17:32,212 --> 00:17:33,692
First, it's a purchasable loot box.

390
00:17:34,672 --> 00:17:36,893
But even if there was geofencing for China,

391
00:17:37,053 --> 00:17:40,174
so that the game didn't have purchasable loot boxes there,

392
00:17:40,674 --> 00:17:42,035
this would still violate their rules,

393
00:17:42,535 --> 00:17:44,056
because this creates a compulsion loop.

394
00:17:44,616 --> 00:17:47,137
Even if the only way to get the loot box was from gameplay,

395
00:17:47,557 --> 00:17:49,898
this encourages the players to purchase the loot box,

396
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:51,198
to get more and more, because they're never

397
00:17:51,238 --> 00:17:52,218
getting what they want out of it.

398
00:17:53,159 --> 00:17:55,159
So that's sort of where the compulsion loop rule

399
00:17:55,219 --> 00:17:55,960
comes in in China.

400
00:17:57,450 --> 00:17:59,191
But of course, as we've seen in China,

401
00:17:59,231 --> 00:18:01,133
particularly with the disclosure requirements,

402
00:18:01,734 --> 00:18:03,035
often those rules aren't enforced.

403
00:18:03,716 --> 00:18:04,797
So maybe the answer here would be

404
00:18:04,817 --> 00:18:07,179
to work with a partner in China who has influence,

405
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:09,722
although that's less successful than it used to be.

406
00:18:12,164 --> 00:18:14,206
So our takeaways for Chinese regulation

407
00:18:14,226 --> 00:18:16,849
is no loot box is purchasable with real money

408
00:18:16,889 --> 00:18:17,790
or virtual currency.

409
00:18:19,156 --> 00:18:23,058
There's flexible and unclear rules that give the government a lot of enforcement power.

410
00:18:23,518 --> 00:18:27,521
And there's a particular focus from the regulatory entities on preventing these compulsion loops.

411
00:18:29,102 --> 00:18:32,904
There's disclosure requirements that exist in China and in Apple's requirements, but

412
00:18:32,924 --> 00:18:36,766
in practice, these requirements can be designed around or simply ignored.

413
00:18:37,926 --> 00:18:41,468
And then that final point is I'd recommend working with a partner who's established in

414
00:18:41,528 --> 00:18:43,690
China if you're doing these practices there.

415
00:18:46,528 --> 00:18:48,229
So to wrap up my presentation today,

416
00:18:48,329 --> 00:18:49,610
how are loot boxes regulated?

417
00:18:49,790 --> 00:18:51,171
Well, it depends on the regulator.

418
00:18:51,631 --> 00:18:53,972
But there's no major regulation in Western countries

419
00:18:54,132 --> 00:18:55,413
outside of Holland and Belgium.

420
00:18:56,013 --> 00:18:57,854
And there's inconsistent enforcement in China.

421
00:18:59,035 --> 00:19:00,135
And that answer is right.

422
00:19:01,356 --> 00:19:02,756
But there's also a second right answer,

423
00:19:02,997 --> 00:19:04,757
which is how loot boxes are regulated

424
00:19:05,278 --> 00:19:07,979
depends on what everyone in this room does going forward.

425
00:19:09,060 --> 00:19:10,180
Just because as of March 2019,

426
00:19:10,220 --> 00:19:12,161
there's no loot box regulation

427
00:19:12,221 --> 00:19:13,462
doesn't mean there won't be tomorrow.

428
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:15,363
And whether you realize it or not,

429
00:19:15,543 --> 00:19:16,943
as a developer or a publisher,

430
00:19:17,303 --> 00:19:19,144
you're a part of a collective dialogue

431
00:19:19,785 --> 00:19:21,325
about how we interact with our players,

432
00:19:21,685 --> 00:19:24,707
our customers, and about how we wanna be regulated.

433
00:19:25,727 --> 00:19:27,108
And so I urge you going forward

434
00:19:27,248 --> 00:19:28,969
to be careful how you use loot boxes

435
00:19:29,309 --> 00:19:31,910
and to take simple steps to prevent problems.

436
00:19:32,670 --> 00:19:34,591
Have parental controls that can be enabled

437
00:19:34,671 --> 00:19:36,612
so that young children don't purchase loot boxes.

438
00:19:37,488 --> 00:19:41,992
You can reach out to players who you think might be exhibiting problematic behavior and

439
00:19:42,012 --> 00:19:44,515
who you also think may not have the money to be doing so.

440
00:19:45,295 --> 00:19:49,739
The simplest and most important thing you can do is when your colleagues or your friends

441
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:54,844
or your parents talk to you about loot boxes, don't paint it as a black and white issue.

442
00:19:55,205 --> 00:19:59,609
Don't just say loot boxes are okay or they're bad because the truth is it's not loot boxes

443
00:19:59,629 --> 00:20:00,309
that are a problem.

444
00:20:01,248 --> 00:20:02,849
which the problem is when loot boxes are used

445
00:20:02,889 --> 00:20:04,970
to do other things, when they're used to create

446
00:20:04,990 --> 00:20:07,151
those compulsion loops to keep players playing longer

447
00:20:07,171 --> 00:20:09,432
than they want to, when they're used to create

448
00:20:09,472 --> 00:20:11,713
pay-to-win mechanics, so players can't win

449
00:20:11,733 --> 00:20:13,314
from their skill or time no matter how long

450
00:20:13,354 --> 00:20:14,015
they play the game.

451
00:20:15,075 --> 00:20:16,816
Loot boxes are a problem when they're not transparent,

452
00:20:16,976 --> 00:20:18,657
when players don't know what's going on.

453
00:20:19,278 --> 00:20:21,819
And when we frame the discussion as solving

454
00:20:21,859 --> 00:20:23,460
these other problems, I think we realize

455
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:25,121
that there's all sorts of game mechanics

456
00:20:25,441 --> 00:20:26,641
that can run into these issues.

457
00:20:27,302 --> 00:20:29,123
And the key is how we use the mechanics,

458
00:20:29,263 --> 00:20:30,143
not whether we use them.

459
00:20:32,180 --> 00:20:34,563
To be clear, I'm not worried about a world

460
00:20:34,643 --> 00:20:35,604
where this is regulated.

